         <abstract>
            <p>The closed form inverse of a tridiagonal matrix, which is a slight generalization of a matrix considered by D. Kershaw (Math. Comp., v. 23, 1969, pp. 189-191), is given in this note. If the matrix has integer elements, an integer multiple of the inverse can be computed by integer arithmetic, that is, without machine roundoff error.</p>
